Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:19.91,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't supposed to be \Nlike this, head in my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:26.25,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Struggling to escape from \Nthis saturated world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:32.01,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes like whispering sand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:35.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,These circumstances, unchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.72,0:00:38.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,gazing out at a dreamless tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.64,0:00:45.81,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna say goodbye to the \Nconfusion of yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.19,0:00:51.23,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,I try reaching out, as if to resist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:56.95,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,We cry millions of times \Nand then get born again
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.24,0:01:00.16,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go with these red eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:03.37,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,to that pictured future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:08.96,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Come here right by me, \NI'm clapping my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.13,0:01:11.05,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.05,0:01:15.42,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Strain my eyes in the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.42,0:01:21.06,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Can't see anything, don't know \Nanything, but I'll still go
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.31,0:01:27.39,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,To the place of shining \Nlight in which you wait
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.39,0:01:29.98,Episode Num,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Five
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.39,0:01:29.98,Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,The Statue of Illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.39,0:01:29.98,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by Ango Sakaguchi’s\NMeijikaika Ango Torimonochou\N(Meiji-era Ango Detective Stories)\N"The Statue of Illusion"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.61,0:01:37.07,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that war has brought the \Nhuman race a number of benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.86,0:01:40.91,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,The development of civilization, \Nthe exchange of cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.62,0:01:42.99,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,House of Representatives Member Shimada Hakurou\N Rising Sun Call to Action Rally
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.91,0:01:42.49,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,and the development of \Nscience and technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.37,0:01:47.04,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Through the control of nuclear power, \Nhave we not acquired the privilege
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.04,0:01:49.21,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,of using air conditioners \Nin the middle of the summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.21,0:01:52.63,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,or watching late-night TV shows?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.25,0:01:56.63,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, I pass on what happened that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.01,0:01:58.26,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,And always will...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.43,0:02:02.89,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,My supporters and I were the \Ntargets of a terrorist bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.89,0:02:04.35,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki said...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.77,0:02:05.97,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,"If an explosion goes off here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.97,0:02:08.48,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,the glass will rain to the \Nground, causing a catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.48,0:02:10.40,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,So we'll move the explosives \Nto another location."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.40,0:02:16.44,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Until mere days before, they \Nwere just ordinary students,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.44,0:02:19.07,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,but they supported me and took \Npart in the Rising Sun Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.07,0:02:22.32,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Without showing any hesitation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.32,0:02:24.66,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,they drove off with the truck \Nthat was loaded with explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.08,0:02:28.46,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,The outcome was just as reported.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.54,0:02:32.63,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not here just to exhort \Nyou to praise the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.92,0:02:35.13,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,They did what should have been done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.59,0:02:39.38,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}But speaking of those \Nthree after the war brings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.42,0:02:37.76,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Are you making fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.26,0:02:41.22,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,I just tried on a formal dress...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:42.85,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}on a mood of hesitation that \Nis definitely not approving.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.63,0:02:42.14,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Sasa Kazamori
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.63,0:02:42.14,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Artificial Intelligence (R.A.I.)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.22,0:02:42.14,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Inga
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.22,0:02:42.14,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Detective's Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.22,0:02:42.68,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,It's cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.85,0:02:44.39,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.85,0:02:44.39,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.85,0:02:44.39,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Komamori... You're a shameless pervert.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.39,0:02:48.27,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Even if the recent war \Nwas a detestable farce,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.72,0:02:46.39,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,You're not pleased?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.39,0:02:49.64,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,T-There's no reason \Nfor you to please me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.27,0:02:52.06,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}those three young men certainly \Nperformed a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.64,0:02:52.06,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:57.82,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,And that most definitely exists \Nin each and every one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:57.61,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Shimada Jirou
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:57.61,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Actor, Son of Mr. Shimada
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.15,0:03:00.65,Main Dialog,MC,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:05.66,Main Dialog,MC,0000,0000,0000,,That was actor Shimada Jirou, the \Noldest son of Shimada Hakurou,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.66,0:03:07.58,Main Dialog,MC,0000,0000,0000,,reading from his father's works.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.58,0:03:11.21,Main Dialog,MC,0000,0000,0000,,Jirou-san has also been appointed \Nhonorary director of the memorial hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:17.25,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let yourselves be \Nfooled by Shimada Hakurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.25,0:03:21.51,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,He's made back room deals with allied \Nnations and lined his own pockets
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.05,0:03:21.51,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Yamamoto Teishin
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.05,0:03:21.51,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Former Bodyguard of Hakurou
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.51,0:03:24.22,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}with financial support collected \Non behalf of the dead youths!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:25.01,Main Dialog,Ootsubo,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yamamoto! We appreciate you \Ncoming all the way out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.51,0:03:25.01,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Ootsubo Tetsuya
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.51,0:03:25.01,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Member of the Rising Sun Party\NHakurou's Bodyguard
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.26,0:03:29.31,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,What about Shimada?! Is he \Nspouting that bullshit again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:32.60,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forget those \Nthree youngsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.60,0:03:34.86,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,and one day, we'll bring \Nabout a miracle, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.86,0:03:37.77,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the symbol \Nof this memorial hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.48,0:03:37.15,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Shimada Hakurou
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.48,0:03:37.15,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Leader of the Rising Sun Party
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.74,0:03:49.29,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Souls...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.79,0:03:57.29,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,I commissioned this statue
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:04:00.76,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,from a young friend of my son's, \None much like those young men.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:03.88,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}It was finally delivered \Nlate last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:03.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Um, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.43,0:04:06.01,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.55,0:04:07.51,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,The bathroom's over...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:10.10,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,The Defeated Detective! Yuuki Shinjurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.10,0:04:13.23,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you're challenging \NJJ Systems' Kaishou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.23,0:04:14.65,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,I commend you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.90,0:04:18.61,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Rumor has it that you \Nhave some connection to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.61,0:04:21.36,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,the young people who were the \Nfirst victims in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:24.53,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Are you the one who invited me here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.53,0:04:26.74,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,There's one thing I dislike.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.74,0:04:28.16,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,What's this "Defeated Detective"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:30.16,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,There is no defeat! This \Nis merely a ceasefire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.16,0:04:31.04,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I have to pee!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.04,0:04:31.87,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.87,0:04:33.25,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me, but I'm about to wet myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.93,0:04:46.97,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.43,0:04:51.10,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,You're a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:53.56,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,It's your duty to reveal the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.06,0:04:58.11,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, when it comes to \Nyourself, you hide it like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.11,0:05:01.53,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,All I want to expose are dirty lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.86,0:05:07.74,Name,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Hirato Youko
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.86,0:05:07.74,Name Sub,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Jirou's Friend, Sculptor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.37,0:05:10.45,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,This is a fancy place to take a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.91,0:05:14.37,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,I was up working 'til the \Nmiddle of the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.37,0:05:14.87,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,...you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.08,0:05:19.71,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,She created the statue \Nand brought it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:22.05,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,This is my good friend, Hirato Youko.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.05,0:05:23.55,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,This is Detective Yuuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.55,0:05:26.55,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. It was worth coming just \Nto look at the statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.59,0:05:31.31,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,"The story is they willingly gave \Nup their lives for someone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.31,0:05:33.14,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't as heroic as all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.47,0:05:35.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,There had to have been \Nat least one tear shed."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.35,0:05:37.73,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I felt \Nwhen I looked at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.73,0:05:41.23,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for my father back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:44.65,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, even though I'm his \Nson, I admit he's too domineering.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:47.11,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,As well as that bit about \Nnot losing the war...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.11,0:05:49.11,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...he's part of the National Service \NRestoration Front or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.11,0:05:50.99,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention he's money-mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.99,0:05:51.95,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Youko!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:55.37,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,That's the opinion of that yakuza \NYamamoto, his former bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:58.46,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,He claims that the story of \Nthe three heroes is a sham,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.08,0:06:01.34,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Wipe Out the Allied Nations' Puppet Government
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.08,0:06:01.34,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Patriotism Justice Victory
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.46,0:06:02.25,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,and that all the donated money was \Nturned into gold bricks and hidden away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:04.84,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,Yamamoto is demanding \Nthe return of the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.13,0:06:07.51,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Gold bricks? That's low.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.51,0:06:10.68,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he was just a member of the \NHouse until recently? I don't buy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:12.22,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.94,0:06:24.52,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,You used the dead to make a profit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.52,0:06:25.98,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,And, this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.98,0:06:27.99,Main Dialog,Ootsubo,0000,0000,0000,,Jirou, sir, don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:29.20,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:33.49,Main Dialog,Ootsubo,0000,0000,0000,,Jirou, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.70,0:06:38.58,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Ootsubo, what is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.80,0:06:49.22,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Gomi
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.80,0:06:49.22,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Former Member of the Rising Sun Party\NWorks for Yamamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.80,0:06:49.22,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Mitsuhisa
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.80,0:06:49.22,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Former Member of the Rising Sun Party\NWorks for Yamamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.47,0:06:53.72,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,They've been murdered... haven't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.10,0:06:59.68,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that things \Nhave gotten interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.68,0:07:02.44,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Because it involves Shimada Hakurou?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.44,0:07:04.94,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't care less about Mr. Shimada.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:06.94,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about the \NDefeated Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.94,0:07:10.11,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Both of the dead were former \Nmembers of the Rising Sun Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.11,0:07:12.07,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Mitsuhisa! Gomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.49,0:07:12.82,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,More recently, they'd \Njoined Yamamoto Sadanobu's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.82,0:07:14.91,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,opposing political organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.91,0:07:19.83,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,How peculiar. Why were those two \Nmurdered and put inside the statue?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.70,0:07:18.87,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.70,0:07:18.87,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Chairman of JJ Systems
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:21.37,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Koyama Izumi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:21.37,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Public Prosecutor\N Joint Coordinating Dept.\N Public Prosecutor's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.83,0:07:21.67,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The Trojan Horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.67,0:07:23.75,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Why were they inside that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.75,0:07:26.92,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,They were your men now! \NWhat are you plotting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.92,0:07:31.93,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a moment! That statue has \Nno real need for an access panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.93,0:07:35.76,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, no one else but the \Ncreator knew that it could open and close.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.10,0:07:40.27,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You killed those two?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:45.19,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Is your side so weak that they \Ngot murdered by this mere girl?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.19,0:07:46.48,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,What's that, you bastard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.48,0:07:47.82,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you insult my men?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.82,0:07:49.69,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't Youko, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:52.65,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Youko to do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.20,0:07:55.87,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I told her to get those \Ntwo into the statue
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.87,0:07:57.66,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,and smuggle them into the memorial hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.41,0:08:01.46,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,You knew about it too, Mr. Yamamoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.54,0:08:05.63,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, under Yamamoto's order,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.63,0:08:09.05,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,the two of them went to find the gold \Nhidden somewhere in the memorial hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.05,0:08:11.92,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the rumored gold bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.92,0:08:16.05,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I see. With a newly-built memorial \Nhall, they could be hidden anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.05,0:08:17.47,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,But why would Jirou help?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.93,0:08:21.77,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Shimada Jirou was repelled by the \Nway his father used the young men,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:24.98,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,who sacrificed their own \Nlives, to publicize himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.52,0:08:28.98,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Gomi-san and Mitsuhisa-san \Nboth knew how I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.69,0:08:34.24,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they asked for my help in \Nstealing the gold and making it public.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:38.37,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Youko to sneak them \Nin Trojan Horse-style.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.24,0:08:43.62,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, the two of them got \Ninside the statue at my studio,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.62,0:08:45.87,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,and I transported it here like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.92,0:08:49.13,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,The whole thing is my responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.13,0:08:53.17,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Jirou, you little shit... You took that \Nbusiness about the gold bricks seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.17,0:08:54.76,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we'll be taking statements...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.76,0:08:55.97,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the issue!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.68,0:08:59.55,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,They say the victims were \Ncarried here with the statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.55,0:09:00.68,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:05.31,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The question is, who \Nkilled the two of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.10,0:09:09.90,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,The plan was for them to get out \Nof the statue before sunrise
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.90,0:09:12.03,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,and look for the gold bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:16.07,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But they were both murdered, and their \Nbodies stuffed back into the statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.45,0:09:19.32,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, Ootsubo and several \Nothers were at the memorial hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.32,0:09:21.49,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,but they were at the security \Ncheckpoint in front of the gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:23.79,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,so no one could have \Ngone off on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.29,0:09:28.25,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,But there was one person remaining, \NShimada Hakurou, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.25,0:09:33.26,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,You're accusing me of killing \NMitsuhisa and Gomi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.01,0:09:36.76,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You were here alone last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:40.01,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You discovered the two of them \Nslipping out of the statue,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.01,0:09:43.60,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,murdered them to protect the gold, and \Nknowing there'd be a lot of trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.60,0:09:45.39,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,put their corpses back into the statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.69,0:09:48.52,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:50.44,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,I believe he's capable of anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.44,0:09:52.94,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you killed three \Nyoung men without even blinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.94,0:09:53.86,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.61,0:09:55.28,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Hayami Seigen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.61,0:09:55.28,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Director of the Security Bureau \NMetropolitan Police Dept.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:55.69,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,It's a well known story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:57.99,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,During the time of that terrorism,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.99,0:10:01.91,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,this man ordered those three to drive \Nthat truck away in no uncertain terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:05.62,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,He did it to create a sense of obligation\N for the supporters who were right there,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:07.50,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,but the truck blew up all too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.16,0:10:10.17,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard! Do you have proof?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.17,0:10:11.04,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.38,0:10:16.42,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that terrorist bombing was \Na put-up job, there's no proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.42,0:10:18.93,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Are you implying that {\i1}I{\i0} used terrorism \Nto murder Suzuki and the others?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:21.09,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say anything for certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.39,0:10:24.18,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But if you did this to \Nprotect the money you made
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.18,0:10:25.93,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,by setting them up as heroes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.93,0:10:30.27,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If you killed for that, you \Nwill find no redemption.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:35.40,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.45,0:10:40.49,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,She's like my boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.49,0:10:43.45,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,You're in high spirits today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.45,0:10:47.00,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I know that pointless deaths \Nlitter the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.54,0:10:49.00,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,There are no heroic tales.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.00,0:10:50.50,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,And no heroes either...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.42,0:10:56.50,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,People have no choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.01,0:10:58.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...but to answer her question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.55,0:11:06.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You must have been worried about whether\N those two would find the gold bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.85,0:11:09.98,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I{\i0} ask the question!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:14.77,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Shimada Jirou, last night you \Ncame back here, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.77,0:11:18.03,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,And what did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.82,0:11:20.53,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:26.20,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You mean he was a witness \Nto the two being murdered?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.20,0:11:27.66,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,We'll find out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.66,0:11:28.79,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:30.66,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,...did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:38.42,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I... returned here when \Nit was still dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:42.47,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I told Ootsubo and the others I \Nwas concerned about the statue...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.47,0:11:44.05,Main Dialog,Ootsubo,0000,0000,0000,,But there was nothing \Nout of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.59,0:11:46.05,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.72,0:11:47.81,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Father was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.81,0:11:49.43,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Shimada Hakurou was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.27,0:11:53.94,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,...sleeping. Just like we planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.23,0:12:02.32,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,I put a sleeping drug \Nin Father's usual tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.95,0:12:05.16,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Enough so that he wouldn't \Nwake 'til morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.16,0:12:08.08,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,The plan was to find the \Ngold bricks before then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:09.99,Main Dialog,Yamamoto,0000,0000,0000,,You say he was sleeping?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.99,0:12:12.12,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I was going to explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.41,0:12:14.75,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I couldn't have killed them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:18.25,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,It's the son's testimony. Perhaps \Nhe's trying to protect his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.25,0:12:19.92,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,If we analyze the remains of the tea...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:23.43,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Humans can't lie when they \Nanswer Inga's question.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.43,0:12:26.59,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Shimada Hakurou didn't murder those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:28.01,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Then who did?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.01,0:12:30.60,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Who killed them, Defeated Detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.60,0:12:37.11,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I believe Yuuki Shinjurou just \Nuncharacteristically jumped to a conclusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.11,0:12:41.32,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of that, for him to decide \Nsomeone is innocent based on testimony...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.32,0:12:43.86,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Still, now that it's come to \Nthis, who is the real killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.86,0:12:46.53,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,What if I said it was "friendly fire"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.53,0:12:47.32,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.32,0:12:50.33,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,The two victims killed each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.95,0:12:53.87,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,They probably squabbled \Nover their shares
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.87,0:12:55.33,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,and by the time of delivery \Nto the memorial hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.33,0:12:57.63,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,they had already breathed their last.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.63,0:12:59.71,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the statue...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.71,0:13:02.63,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,This way, Mr. Shimada \Ndoesn't get hurt, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.63,0:13:04.13,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,This is how you want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.13,0:13:08.34,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe after this, Mr. Shimada \Nwill settle down a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.85,0:13:13.43,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,That idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.43,0:13:16.94,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Shinjurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.94,0:13:21.19,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Buy me ice cream! Ice cream!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.19,0:13:23.49,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,A soul like that still leaves me hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:24.57,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.40,0:13:27.70,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,There are no tales of \Nheroism on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.32,0:13:30.58,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you think I killed them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.58,0:13:35.16,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You were either threatening them... \Nor you planned the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.16,0:13:38.08,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Then let's assume that it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.71,0:13:42.71,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,But they died... to save \Na great number of lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.30,0:13:45.34,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Other than that, what more is necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:49.34,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Or perhaps they were terrified of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.34,0:13:53.68,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,screamed the names of their \Nsweethearts, and pissed their pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.68,0:13:57.02,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Still, did the driver take \Nhis foot off the gas pedal?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.02,0:14:00.31,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone wants to live. Naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.56,0:14:05.74,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, in that instant, they chose \Nto save all the people that were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.15,0:14:08.24,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,If they wanted to escape, \Nthey could have...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.24,0:14:09.95,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,But they didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.78,0:14:14.79,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that they acted \Nwithout an ulterior motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.79,0:14:16.00,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,From the bottom of my heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.00,0:14:19.00,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to pass that down through \Nthe generations as a heroic tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.00,0:14:24.05,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Youngster, you don't know \Nthe true beauty of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.51,0:14:35.77,Name White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.51,0:14:35.77,Name Sub White,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Daughter of Kaishou Rinroku,\NLives at Home
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.51,0:14:35.77,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,According to my father, the murder \Nwas a result of "friendly fire".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.77,0:14:37.14,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.23,0:14:41.06,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it's just another lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.06,0:14:44.15,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Shimada Hakurou has \Npull in the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.15,0:14:45.36,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Father just wants to \Nput him in his debt!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.90,0:14:48.28,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to \Ndo anything about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.24,0:15:00.04,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,You thought Mr. Shimada was the culprit \Nfrom the beginning, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.71,0:15:03.88,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't forgive him for being \Nthe kind of person who claims that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:07.30,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,"war is the right thing to do" and \N"giving up your life is wonderful".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.80,0:15:09.55,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,But, you were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.55,0:15:13.93,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That's right. From the get-go,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.93,0:15:16.47,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't picture anybody \Nbut him being the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.47,0:15:19.81,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But afterwards I couldn't even \Nthink of one word to refute him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:21.19,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Refute him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.81,0:15:27.65,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,To what he said about people being able \Nto give up their lives for other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.65,0:15:30.61,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't believe in stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:36.03,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,People live with things they don't \Ntalk about hidden in their heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.45,0:15:40.46,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I thought my job was to bring \Nthose things to light...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.79,0:15:42.75,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...but now, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:47.13,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,You really are the Defeated \NDetective, Yuuki Shinjurou.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:51.09,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I... had expectations for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.09,0:15:53.05,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I thought maybe it would be you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.05,0:15:57.22,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,who could destroy the wall we \Nall sense, but cannot see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:01.23,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Well, don't count on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.73,0:16:04.02,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I know myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.02,0:16:09.57,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a fool, and powerless, and... \NI can't do anything for anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.03,0:16:17.99,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:20.50,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,You're not gonna quit being \Na detective, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:24.33,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you're gonna let \Nme eat lots of souls, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.29,0:16:27.67,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjurou...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.88,0:16:30.67,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,It's odd, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:33.76,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Humans really are peculiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.18,0:16:37.80,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that even with all the \Ndata in the world, you don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.80,0:16:41.81,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,You thought that Shimada's heroic \Nlegend was a made up fairy tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:45.23,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But it was the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:47.27,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The essence is unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.94,0:16:49.98,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It's just something beautiful \Nthat's been sullied.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.53,0:16:53.28,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you with Inga?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:56.49,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,So he can feed me souls!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.49,0:16:56.95,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Inga!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:16:58.78,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Without having to kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.78,0:17:01.41,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about how you and Inga met.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.41,0:17:02.87,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I'm me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:06.33,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that in exchange \Nfor Inga not murdering anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:10.34,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,you give him souls; people's truths. {oh, i didn't realize that inga changed gender when she transformed? I figured she was just a cute little androgynous girl that turned into a buxomy crazy chick... are you sure these male pronouns are correct? please let me know either way so i can be clear for future episodes}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:14.97,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,But that obviously means \Nhaving him haunt you. {him her please let me know}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.30,0:17:17.97,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,So what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.18,0:17:23.22,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that giving up your own life \Nfor the sake of other people?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:29.56,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not that noble...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:32.07,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,In my mind, it's just \Nabout the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:33.90,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I give you the percentage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.99,0:17:44.37,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,The real culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.37,0:17:46.33,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Those two didn't kill each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.58,0:17:48.67,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It was actually quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.67,0:17:51.38,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I wasn't looking \Nat the illusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.88,0:17:54.17,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The real murderer's illusion is the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.17,0:17:56.47,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,that those two snuck in so they \Ncould steal the gold bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.47,0:17:58.13,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.13,0:18:01.39,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Before the statue was transported, \Nbefore they got inside of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.39,0:18:02.72,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,they were already murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:05.60,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.60,0:18:06.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...who could have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.44,0:18:09.94,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I do something so heinous?! {not really sure this merits and interobang}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.94,0:18:10.98,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.98,0:18:12.11,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,She has no motive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:13.98,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,As I said, it's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.98,0:18:16.32,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Her purpose was the gold bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.32,0:18:17.49,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:21.82,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,During yesterday's party, you were \Nthe only one in the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.82,0:18:22.99,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,I was tired!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.24,0:18:27.37,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Even with all the ruckus outside, \Nyou didn't leave the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.71,0:18:31.58,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Even though bodies fell out of \Nthe statue that you created?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.58,0:18:34.05,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to... \Nbe wrongly suspected!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.05,0:18:38.26,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,From where you were lying, you could \Nclearly see Shimada Hakurou's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.59,0:18:40.84,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,My back?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:42.60,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Corpses from a statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.60,0:18:45.14,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,A person with good sense \Nwould suspect robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:46.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,And so, it's only natural \Nthat you would look
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.85,0:18:49.02,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,straight at the place where something \Nprecious was hidden, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:52.73,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You kept an eye on Mr. Shimada \Nto see which way he would face.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.73,0:18:55.36,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But he didn't move at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.36,0:18:56.61,Main Dialog,Jirou,0000,0000,0000,,Youko...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.61,0:18:59.74,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You knew that the gold bricks \Nhadn't been stolen yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.32,0:19:02.99,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...since you'd already killed those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.99,0:19:04.87,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want any gold bricks!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.87,0:19:08.62,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that the three who \Ndied are any kind of heroes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:11.17,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,They were crying and screamed \Nthat they didn't want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:13.29,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,They were just ordinary kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.29,0:19:15.34,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I helped with your plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.34,0:19:16.50,Main Dialog,Youko,0000,0000,0000,,That's the only reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.88,0:19:18.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:23.14,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't in the design.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.14,0:19:26.06,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was a \Nmessage from the artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:26.85,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.35,0:19:30.27,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,It's human blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.14,0:19:32.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If the police check it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.77,0:19:35.02,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they'll find it \Nbelongs to one of the victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:37.98,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If they'd murdered each \Nother inside the statue,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.98,0:19:40.03,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,there's no way there would be a \Nsplash of blood on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:44.62,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,They were murdered outside of the \Nstatue, before it was transported.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:49.33,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The interior of the statue \Nheats up in the daytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.33,0:19:52.33,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,And so, figuring out the exact \Ntime of death would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.50,0:19:56.96,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The tear that I saw \Nwas also an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.13,0:20:01.17,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.17,0:20:02.84,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.84,0:20:07.64,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't afford to let Mr. \NShimada come off unscathed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.64,0:20:11.89,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,To be fooled by a beautiful \Nwoman... Some detective he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.23,0:20:15.19,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I owe you my thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.48,0:20:18.48,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I just came here to sully \Nsomething that was beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:21.03,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that woman is beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.03,0:20:26.70,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,Or that you still doubt the beauty of \Nthose young men giving up their lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:28.95,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, they died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:31.45,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm alive. And so are you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.95,0:20:33.54,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.54,0:20:37.17,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,People have given up \Ntheir lives for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.17,0:20:39.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't say a damn \Nthing about either one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.88,0:20:42.22,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones who are admirable... \Nwho are beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.80,0:20:44.68,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...are the guys that died!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.68,0:20:48.30,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of us are petty, \Nand stupid, and vulgar...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.30,0:20:51.43,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,...and grovel on the ground as \Nwe desperately try to stay alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.43,0:20:52.35,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.60,0:20:53.89,Main Dialog,Shimada,0000,0000,0000,,You little...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.89,0:20:57.86,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you didn't panic, even \Nafter finding out about the thieves...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.90,0:20:59.69,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Inga.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.90,0:21:01.90,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.33,0:21:18.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,It was in front of you all the time. \NThere was no need to lose your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.59,0:21:36.14,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,In the pale morning \Nmist, a whispered prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.52,0:21:44.15,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna follow this \Ntwisted landscape with you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.61,0:21:52.16,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the "truth", \N"a 'lie' will do" is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.49,0:22:00.58,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Tracing it as if we can see through
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.58,0:22:04.46,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, beyond words
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.46,0:22:08.47,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a falling feather
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.47,0:22:11.47,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.39,0:22:16.89,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.20,0:22:36.33,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, unravel it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.33,0:22:40.46,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a tattered cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.46,0:22:43.29,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.17,0:22:48.51,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.01,0:22:54.06,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode is inspired from \N"Meiji-era Ango Detective Stories"...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.06,0:22:55.14,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's not?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.14,0:22:57.85,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,The original work is a \Nshort story called "Angou"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.85,0:22:59.73,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,The title has a double \Nmeaning, both "angou",
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.73,0:23:02.06,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,which means a code to hide secrets and \Nthen, of course, the author's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.06,0:23:04.07,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,But who cares about that? \NI'll give it a read.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.32,0:23:09.70,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,It's a great story! I've got \Ntears coming from my eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.70,0:23:12.66,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe Shinjurou and I
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.66,0:23:17.45,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,are going to tamper with a \Nwonderful story like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.75,0:23:22.27,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on UN-GO, \N"The Code Too Simple"!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.53,0:23:23.97,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,What a great feeling...
